Title: Write a short text adventure.
Description: Write possible actions in a text adventure.
Input.context: Long ago the bombs fell and the world ended. You are one of the few who is still alive. You are trying to survive by scavenging among the ruins of what is left behind.
Input.story_block_1: You search the cars for food, you search three without success, but in the glove compartment of the fourth you find a box of crackers.
Input.story_block_2: They remind you of when you needed to eat a bland diet after your operation. You pat yourself on where you remember the incision was made. The scar healed long ago, but the brain remembers. The crackers weren't very nutritious, but some fuel in the tank is better than none.
Input.previous_action_2: Continue to look for food in the building up ahead.
Answer.result: You find a moldy sandwich and some peppered beef jerky in an old lunchbox.

Title: Write a short text adventure.

Input.context: Long ago the bombs fell and the world ended. You are one of the few who is still alive. You are trying to survive by scavenging among the ruins of what is left behind.
Input.story_block_1: It looks like the store has been ransacked and all the shelves are empty. You manage to find a package of granola bars and a flashlight behind the counter.
Input.story_block_2: It tastes just like a granola bar you enjoyed when you were younger. In an instant, you are transported to a school hiking trip. Your mind is awash by the mountain air and the bundles of sticks and leaves that formed the trail. Those days seem so long ago now...
Input.previous_action_2: Look for other doors inside the store.
Answer.result: You find the store manager's door, with a set of keys hanging off the lock. The door, though, seems to be blocked from the inside.
